Wylie Brys and his dad, Dallas zookeeper Tim Brys, were digging for fossils near a local grocery store when they made the discovery in September . 
 After seven months, they acquired permits to dig up the bones . 
 Scientists from Southern Methodist University are helping with excavation . 
 Fossils are expected for be from a nodosaur, a pony-sized herbivore with scaly, plated skin . 
 